window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>ZionLine's promise was irresistible: triple your lifespan. The price? Surviving an unknown world rife with brutal combat, where the gruesome deaths are terrifyingly real. For a desperate humanity, it was a price worth paying....</b></p> <p><b>But beneath the time dilation's gleaming facade lies a horrific truth that Earth's elite will kill to conceal. They will fail. Raine KongRu has seen this future before. He lived through the yoke of captivity it heralds, and he knows there is precious little time to consolidate his power before millions die—again.</b></p> <p>Enemies multiply as events outside Raine’s memories proliferate. But he wouldn’t have it any other way, for Raine’s martial path is one of challenge, pressure, and risk. The more on the line, the faster he evolves to meet the tidal wave of forces arrayed against him.</p> <p>Under the guise of Alaric, Raine is hunted by those with the means to see him dead in both worlds. CronGate was once his home, its leaders his mentors, its people his own. They taught him everything he knew, and enslaved him for a lifetime. Now, CronGate’s vast financial might is aimed directly at his throat, and they’ll stop at nothing to ensure Raine KongRu, and Alaric, become just another footnote in history.</p> <p>The feeling is mutual.</p> <p><b>What you can expect to find in Martial Messiah:</b></p> <ul> <li><b>High-Stakes Tension: </b>A VRMMO adventure where the danger grips you by the collar and doesn’t let go.</li> <li><b>Complex Systems: </b>Deep LitRPG mechanics and multiple layers of magic systems that don’t stop just because you’re back on Earth.</li> <li><b>A Living World: </b>Actions have logical, rippling consequences. No plot armor. No contrived BS. Non-stop easy outs.</li> <li><b>A Mature Protagonist: </b>Raine KongRu isn't afraid of building meaningful relationships. He faces the women in his life with confidence and conviction, avoiding the common tropes of the genre.</li> </ul> <p><b>So, what are you waiting for? Come, seeker of adventure. Dive into book two of Martial Messiah and experience a non-stop thrill ride that will leave you thirsty for more, more, more.</b></p>"; 
